title: Angèle (singer)
summary: Angèle Van Laeken (French: [ɑ̃ʒɛl]) (Dutch pronunciation: [vɑn ˈlaːkə(n)]; born 3 December 1995) is a Belgian singer. She was one of 2018's biggest breakout acts in French and Belgian pop music, breaking Stromae's record for weeks at the top of the Belgian singles charts with her 2018 single "Tout oublier" which features her brother, Roméo Elvis.
